PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775823080
OL,3,CHip-hop pioneer Afrika Bambaataa dies
OL,4,Caged 68
OL,6,FBy the 1980s, his parties were
OL,7,Fattracting huge crowds, and he began
OL,8,Freleasing his own records that helped
OL,9,Fshape the burgeoning hip-hop and
OL,10,Felectro-funk music movements.
OL,12,FHe eventually formed the group Zulu
OL,13,FNation, a nod to a South African
OL,14,Fethnic group that he drew inspiration
OL,15,Ffrom. His slogan eventually became
OL,16,Fknown as "peace, love, unity and
OL,17,Fhaving fun," and he said that he
OL,18,Fsought to use hip-hop's ballooning
OL,19,Fpopularity to resolve local gang
OL,20,Fconflicts.
OL,26,@xD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
